230
00:14:44.692 --> 00:14:46.435
They said they want to come
to our restaurant!

231
00:14:46.435 --> 00:14:47.711
I really want them to come!

232
00:14:47.711 --> 00:14:50.755
This is amazing.
Chef Ohn, you're a star!

233
00:14:50.755 --> 00:14:52.447
False hopes are forbidden!

234
00:14:52.447 --> 00:14:55.230
Even so, tomorrow may be
different than yesterday!

235
00:14:55.230 --> 00:14:56.230
Let's go! Yeah!

236
00:14:56.230 --> 00:14:57.980
Let's get ready for what
the future may have in store!

237
00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.567
- Let's get ready!
- Let's get ready!

238
00:15:00.547 --> 00:15:02.163
I want to watch "Foul Detective" now.

239
00:15:17.787 --> 00:15:19.596
- Get out.
- Here?

240
00:15:19.596 --> 00:15:22.224
Are you planning to die with me, then?

241
00:15:46.398 --> 00:15:49.356
Ugh, how boring.

242
00:15:49.356 --> 00:15:52.287
I'm sure the ratings will have
dropped like crazy by tomorrow.

243
00:15:52.287 --> 00:15:56.395
Why do they keep having
explosions, fires, and fights?

244
00:15:57.393 --> 00:15:59.666
They threw out pretty much
all of what I wrote.

245
00:16:03.096 --> 00:16:05.769
They had writers who were
working on this beforehand, Hyun Soo.

246
00:16:07.904 --> 00:16:09.471
You'll get through this.

247
00:16:09.471 --> 00:16:12.625
You're still the one being credited with
the writing. Who'll know?

248
00:16:12.625 --> 00:16:13.941
I will.

249
00:16:13.941 --> 00:16:15.998
It might as well be everyone.

250
00:16:16.844 --> 00:16:18.584
Where are you going?

251
00:16:18.584 --> 00:16:20.259
I need to go see for myself.

252
00:16:20.259 --> 00:16:22.486
I can't just make judgment calls
based off assumptions.

253
00:16:27.645 --> 00:16:29.046
Oh, Writer Lee.

254
00:16:29.046 --> 00:16:31.890
We edited tomorrow's episode.
I didn't even have the chance to go home

255
00:16:31.890 --> 00:16:33.121
because we finished the shoot so late.

256
00:16:33.121 --> 00:16:34.371
I saw the episode.

257
00:16:35.550 --> 00:16:39.975
Yi Bok was working on this with other
writers, not just Writer Park.

258
00:16:39.975 --> 00:16:43.322
It would've been nice if someone
had told me about that beforehand.

259
00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:46.452
Just think about this realistically.

260
00:16:46.452 --> 00:16:47.880
Just deal with it!

261
00:16:47.880 --> 00:16:50.041
The writing is being
credited to you, anyway.

262
00:16:50.041 --> 00:16:51.760
You'll be a writer who has
a mini-series that was on the air!

263
00:16:51.760 --> 00:16:54.854
It'll be easier for you
next time around.

264
00:17:03.265 --> 00:17:05.997
<i>Even up until the point that
I quit working at the company...</i>

265
00:17:05.997 --> 00:17:08.861
<i>I thought that I'd become
a writer immediately.</i>

266
00:17:10.525 --> 00:17:12.567
I like Yeouido.

267
00:17:13.612 --> 00:17:15.849
I told myself that I'd dance
in Yeouido Park

268
00:17:15.849 --> 00:17:19.033
if I was chosen as a winner
of the open call.

269
00:17:21.144 --> 00:17:22.520
Get lots of rest.

270
00:17:22.520 --> 00:17:24.099
You're dishonest.

271
00:17:24.099 --> 00:17:26.546
You pretend that you're kind, care
for others, and that you work hard.

272
00:17:26.546 --> 00:17:29.215
But I've never met someone as
wicked as you in my 10 years as a writer.

273
00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:30.827
You want to become a writer, huh?

274
00:17:30.827 --> 00:17:32.897
Yeah, you'll probably make it.

275
00:17:33.812 --> 00:17:37.842
<i>Usually, the nasty bitches like you
are the ones that make it in this field!</i>

276
00:17:37.842 --> 00:17:40.946
And Writer Lee is no ordinary person.

277
00:17:40.946 --> 00:17:42.955
You know too, since
you've seen it for yourself!

278
00:17:42.955 --> 00:17:46.067
She looks so gentle and smiles a lot,
so I thought she was a kind person.

279
00:17:47.842 --> 00:17:51.197
<i>- They got new writers.
- They've been using other writers.</i>

280
00:17:51.197 --> 00:17:55.310
<i>Ms. Lee Hyun Soo, who always changes her
mind, saying humans are insignificant.</i>

281
00:17:55.310 --> 00:17:59.248
<i>Ms. Lee Hyun Soo, who pushes away the
man who loves her because of reality.</i>

282
00:18:07.437 --> 00:18:09.792
CEO Park.

283
00:18:09.792 --> 00:18:12.650
The episode that aired today wasn't
based on Hyun Soo's script.

284
00:18:12.650 --> 00:18:15.423
The ratings are higher than
they were last week.

285
00:18:15.423 --> 00:18:17.754
Things will probably get
difficult for Writer Lee.

286
00:18:21.272 --> 00:18:22.913
Do you think she'll be fired?

287
00:18:22.913 --> 00:18:24.702
No.

288
00:18:24.702 --> 00:18:26.795
It's Writer Lee's story,
so how could they fire her?

289
00:18:26.795 --> 00:18:29.796
They'll leave her name on there, but
the ghostwriter will keep writing.

290
00:18:29.796 --> 00:18:31.622
That's a relief!

291
00:18:31.622 --> 00:18:34.746
I was so scared that she'd be fired
since so many crazy things are happening.

292
00:18:35.852 --> 00:18:40.196
I came to ask you to stop that from
happening, just in case.

293
00:18:41.174 --> 00:18:42.651
Geez!

294
00:18:42.651 --> 00:18:45.716
Geez!
Ugh, I'm so tired!

295
00:18:45.716 --> 00:18:46.975
Ugh, I'm so worn out!

296
00:18:46.975 --> 00:18:50.026
Hey, hey, move it!
Ugh.

297
00:18:50.026 --> 00:18:52.265
I hate all of the people
from the broadcasting company!

298
00:18:52.265 --> 00:18:53.622
Why are you being like that?

299
00:18:54.775 --> 00:18:57.176
I'll get going now, CEO Park.

300
00:18:57.244 --> 00:18:59.072
Did you not hear me,
Ms. Kyung?

301
00:18:59.072 --> 00:19:00.696
Excuse me!
Ms. Kyung!

302
00:19:00.696 --> 00:19:02.053
Hey!

303
00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:04.081
Who's writing the script now?

304
00:19:04.081 --> 00:19:06.039
There's a team of three
people writing it.

305
00:19:07.123 --> 00:19:09.385
They won't be able to fire Hyun Soo
if she doesn't quit herself.

306
00:19:09.385 --> 00:19:10.697
So tell her to just hang in there.

307
00:19:10.697 --> 00:19:14.100
And that this contempt will
surely bring her glory later.

308
00:19:14.706 --> 00:19:19.013
What good will it do her to get glory
if she's broken inside?

309
00:19:20.949 --> 00:19:22.413
Are you going to stay here?

310
00:19:22.413 --> 00:19:23.830
Are you going somewhere?

311
00:19:26.080 --> 00:19:27.933
There's someone I need to meet up with.

312
00:19:45.834 --> 00:19:48.221
Congrats. People loved you.

313
00:19:48.221 --> 00:19:49.594
Ugh.

314
00:19:49.594 --> 00:19:51.552
I'm sure you're still giddy about it.

315
00:19:51.552 --> 00:19:53.228
Chef Ohn Jung Seon.

316
00:19:54.623 --> 00:19:57.571
I don't know if I deserve to be
congratulated for this.

317
00:19:57.571 --> 00:19:58.840
It is something to be
congratulated for.

318
00:19:58.840 --> 00:20:00.706
They're all enamored by you,
even though they don't even know you.

319
00:20:00.706 --> 00:20:02.957
- You think so?
- Yeah.

320
00:20:02.957 --> 00:20:04.965
You're now loved by everyone
without even trying.

321
00:20:05.898 --> 00:20:07.775
It's all thanks to you.

322
00:20:07.775 --> 00:20:09.428
It's definitely worth celebrating.

323
00:20:09.428 --> 00:20:10.835
And it had nothing to do with luck.

324
00:20:18.596 --> 00:20:20.885
Did you come here this late at night
to congratulate me?

325
00:20:20.885 --> 00:20:22.515
Well, that, too.

326
00:20:22.515 --> 00:20:24.448
But I had a favor to ask of you.

327
00:20:24.448 --> 00:20:25.661
What is it?

328
00:20:25.661 --> 00:20:27.875
I want to propose to someone.

329
00:20:27.875 --> 00:20:31.042
When?
And, to whom?

330
00:20:31.042 --> 00:20:34.760
I usually make the really
important decisions by myself.

331
00:20:34.760 --> 00:20:38.056
Wow, this woman who is really
important to you must be happy.

332
00:20:39.413 --> 00:20:41.142
Do you really think so?

333
00:20:41.142 --> 00:20:43.448
Yeah. You really are a
man among men.

334
00:20:45.181 --> 00:20:46.938
I want to do it at Good Soup.

335
00:20:46.938 --> 00:20:50.343
Go ahead. I'll make it
super fancy for you.

336
00:20:50.343 --> 00:20:51.667
Thanks.

337
00:21:01.654 --> 00:21:03.392
- You're curious, right?
- Yeah.

338
00:21:09.016 --> 00:21:10.041
Were you sleeping?

339
00:21:10.041 --> 00:21:11.347
Yeah.
What's going on?

340
00:21:11.347 --> 00:21:12.690
Why are all of you here?

341
00:21:12.690 --> 00:21:14.985
Bo Ra!

342
00:21:14.985 --> 00:21:16.972
I heard there was an article
about you, Aunt!

343
00:21:16.972 --> 00:21:18.027
Bo Ra!

344
00:21:18.027 --> 00:21:19.777
Stop it, Mom.
You'll scare her.

345
00:21:20.675 --> 00:21:22.820
Oh, you're so good at talking, Bo Ra!

346
00:21:22.820 --> 00:21:25.556
She talks at a level that is way above
an average four-year-old's.

347
00:21:25.556 --> 00:21:26.652
Right?

348
00:21:27.457 --> 00:21:28.632
Yeah.

349
00:21:28.632 --> 00:21:29.902
She takes after her aunt.

350
00:21:29.902 --> 00:21:31.350
Hyun Soo was just like that.

351
00:21:31.350 --> 00:21:35.015
Yeah, Hyun Soo has been really clever
ever since she was young.

352
00:21:35.015 --> 00:21:38.190
If I heard you all say this before I got
married, I would've thrown a fit.

353
00:21:38.190 --> 00:21:41.103
I really like my brother-in-law
and have a lot of love for him

354
00:21:41.103 --> 00:21:44.524
but the one thing I always want to ask
is, why would he marry Hyun Yi?

355
00:21:44.524 --> 00:21:46.652
- Big Sis.
- Just look.

356
00:21:46.652 --> 00:21:48.722
Back then, she would've
kicked me for that.

357
00:21:50.085 --> 00:21:51.745
What was the article about?

358
00:21:53.937 --> 00:21:57.818
I heard that you wrote the show
with someone else.

359
00:21:57.818 --> 00:21:58.962
Yeah.

360
00:21:58.962 --> 00:22:00.856
Hyun Yi is really good
at this kind of thing.

361
00:22:00.856 --> 00:22:03.054
Saying the things that are
difficult to say.

362
00:22:07.315 --> 00:22:08.781
You didn't know?

363
00:22:08.781 --> 00:22:10.825
No, I did, but it still hurts.

364
00:22:11.810 --> 00:22:13.652
It still hurts.

365
00:22:14.681 --> 00:22:18.536
But you got a show you wrote on the air!
You're doing so much better than before.

366
00:22:19.695 --> 00:22:21.916
Let's eat this, Mom.

367
00:22:21.916 --> 00:22:24.087
We have to feed her.
If we do, she'll feel better.

368
00:22:24.087 --> 00:22:25.590
Right, Bo Ra?

369
00:22:25.590 --> 00:22:27.255
Oh, you're such a cutie.

370
00:22:33.690 --> 00:22:35.187
Yes. I understand.

371
00:22:35.187 --> 00:22:38.966
One reservation for two guests on Sunday,
October 14th, at 7 p.m. has been made.

372
00:22:38.966 --> 00:22:40.996
- Make some fillets!
- All right!

373
00:22:59.319 --> 00:23:00.574
Yes, this is Good Soup.

374
00:23:00.574 --> 00:23:02.930
- All done!
- Cool it down!

375
00:23:04.511 --> 00:23:06.459
We're short on fillets.
We need to make more.

376
00:23:06.459 --> 00:23:07.570
We're packed for lunch, too.

377
00:23:07.570 --> 00:23:08.705
Yes, Chef.

378
00:23:08.705 --> 00:23:11.460
- Two steaks for table 10.
- Yes, Chef.

379
00:23:15.363 --> 00:23:16.541
Wow.

380
00:23:16.541 --> 00:23:17.798
My blood sugar is so low that
I taste sweetness in my mouth.

381
00:23:17.798 --> 00:23:18.832
- Mm.
- Wow.

382
00:23:18.832 --> 00:23:20.261
You guys are so energetic.

383
00:23:20.261 --> 00:23:22.687
I guess the differences between us
are getting clearer now.

384
00:23:23.444 --> 00:23:24.635
You guessed it yourself, Sous Chef!

385
00:23:24.635 --> 00:23:26.170
Stop that, already.

386
00:23:26.170 --> 00:23:27.735
You always have to confirm
people's beliefs.

387
00:23:27.735 --> 00:23:29.232
Hey, you're even worse!

388
00:23:31.300 --> 00:23:33.379
You said all of our dinner reservations
are booked, right?

389
00:23:33.379 --> 00:23:35.963
Yes. We're almost fully booked
for this entire week, too.

390
00:23:35.963 --> 00:23:40.340
- Wow!
- Wow!

391
00:23:40.340 --> 00:23:41.516
Chef.

392
00:23:41.516 --> 00:23:44.089
We can't just let
this historical day pass us by!

393
00:23:44.089 --> 00:23:45.365
Nope!

394
00:23:45.365 --> 00:23:46.972
Let's sweat it out later
and celebrate.

395
00:23:46.972 --> 00:23:48.000
Sound good?

396
00:23:48.000 --> 00:23:50.116
- Sounds great!
- Sounds great!

397
00:23:59.140 --> 00:24:02.372
<font color="#80ffff">[DF Ver] E14 Temperature of Love "Then Give Up on Me"</font>
<font color="#ff80ff">-= Ruo Xi =-</font>

398
00:24:11.415 --> 00:24:12.832
<i>Endure it.</i>

399
00:24:12.832 --> 00:24:14.652
Yeah, endure it.

400
00:24:14.652 --> 00:24:15.885
Endure it.

401
00:24:15.885 --> 00:24:17.462
Oh, how cute.

402
00:24:17.462 --> 00:24:19.977
- Should I endure it?
- Endure it!

403
00:24:21.192 --> 00:24:22.968
- You need to say it, too.
- Hm?

404
00:24:23.473 --> 00:24:25.901
Um, yeah.
Do as you please.

405
00:24:48.411 --> 00:24:50.334
<i>What is it that you want to say?</i>

406
00:24:52.017 --> 00:24:54.283
I'll quit.

407
00:24:54.740 --> 00:24:57.527
I'll withdraw from the production
of "Foul Detective."

408
00:24:58.709 --> 00:25:01.283
Why are you being like this,
Writer Lee?

409
00:25:01.283 --> 00:25:04.767
I told you to think realistically! You
only need to endure it for a short while!

410
00:25:04.767 --> 00:25:06.116
I can't.

411
00:25:06.116 --> 00:25:08.617
I have no idea why I should endure.

412
00:25:09.631 --> 00:25:11.150
I'm sorry.

413
00:25:12.189 --> 00:25:14.716
You were so kind to me, Chief Producer.

414
00:25:16.773 --> 00:25:18.325
But I give up.

415
00:25:18.325 --> 00:25:20.978
You'll regret it!

416
00:25:20.978 --> 00:25:24.722
If you want to survive in this industry
and be a part of it, listen to me!

417
00:25:25.373 --> 00:25:27.021
Thank you.

418
00:25:43.479 --> 00:25:46.118
<i>I hate emotionally
upsetting other people.</i>

419
00:25:47.420 --> 00:25:49.782
<i>Why should I be the only person
who gives you a guarantee?</i>

420
00:25:51.257 --> 00:25:52.746
<i>I'm scared.</i>

421
00:25:53.366 --> 00:25:55.786
<i>There's nothing stopping a woman
who dumped me once...</i>

422
00:25:55.786 --> 00:25:57.891
<i>from dumping me again.</i>

423
00:26:02.584 --> 00:26:05.645
<i>[Ohn Jung Seon]</i>

424
00:26:12.056 --> 00:26:13.526
- Whoa!
- Hey!

425
00:26:13.526 --> 00:26:15.283
- Go, go!
- Hey!

426
00:26:15.283 --> 00:26:16.744
Yeah!

427
00:26:25.659 --> 00:26:28.363
<i>[Lee Hyun Soo]</i>

428
00:26:39.342 --> 00:26:41.195
<i>[Lee Hyun Soo]</i>

429
00:26:45.144 --> 00:26:47.276
<i>[CEO Park Jung Woo]</i>

430
00:26:49.373 --> 00:26:51.021
Yes, CEO Park?

431
00:26:51.021 --> 00:26:53.636
Looks like you caused trouble again,
Writer Lee Hyun Soo.

432
00:26:54.379 --> 00:26:56.300
I got a call from
Chief Producer Yoo Hong Jin.

433
00:26:56.300 --> 00:26:58.263
Are you really going to be like this?

434
00:26:58.729 --> 00:27:00.093
Come to the office!

435
00:27:12.454 --> 00:27:15.033
If you have something you
want to say, then say it.

436
00:27:16.380 --> 00:27:18.488
Hurry up and scold me.
I want to leave.

437
00:27:25.334 --> 00:27:29.058
Why do you think that
I'm going to scold you?

438
00:27:30.795 --> 00:27:33.001
Because I couldn't endure.

439
00:27:33.990 --> 00:27:35.919
I never told you to endure, though.

440
00:27:43.093 --> 00:27:46.791
You rejected all of my
goodwill toward you.

441
00:27:48.599 --> 00:27:50.106
You said that you'd do it yourself.

442
00:27:50.106 --> 00:27:52.148
You made me do something
that I couldn't handle.

443
00:27:54.719 --> 00:27:57.629
Do you know how difficult it is...

444
00:27:57.629 --> 00:27:59.723
to say that you can't
endure something?

445
00:28:00.399 --> 00:28:02.717
Everyone else told me
to hang in there.

446
00:28:03.781 --> 00:28:06.467
But that isn't the work
that I wrote.

447
00:28:08.084 --> 00:28:10.110
That's not what I wanted to say.

448
00:28:10.798 --> 00:28:13.588
But they said that everything will be
solved if I just endured this.

449
00:28:14.469 --> 00:28:16.753
How does that make any sense?

450
00:28:20.736 --> 00:28:23.437
I endured this because I wanted
my work to be on TV.

451
00:28:26.136 --> 00:28:27.694
Director Min...

452
00:28:28.291 --> 00:28:31.386
sent me multiple signs indicating
that he had different thoughts.

453
00:28:31.386 --> 00:28:34.206
But I ignored it, because
I wanted to like him.

454
00:28:37.698 --> 00:28:40.122
"Writer: Lee Hyun Soo."

455
00:28:42.658 --> 00:28:45.046
If my name was credited on the
project like that...

456
00:28:46.392 --> 00:28:50.294
my parents would be happy, and those
around me would see me in a new light.

457
00:28:53.880 --> 00:28:58.043
I threw away the innocent thought of
wanting to tell my story while I held on.

458
00:29:02.405 --> 00:29:04.132
I felt that, if I endured this...

459
00:29:06.041 --> 00:29:11.019
I thought it'd be difficult to return to
being to the person I truly want to be.

460
00:29:16.633 --> 00:29:18.969
Was that so wrong of me?

461
00:29:51.604 --> 00:29:53.236
Oh, I told myself I wasn't going to cry.

462
00:30:07.273 --> 00:30:12.273
Subtitles by DramaFever

463
00:30:21.443 --> 00:30:23.715
<i>[Temperature of Love]</i>

464
00:30:23.944 --> 00:30:27.050
<i>We've gotten some good conditions
from our negotiation.</i>

465
00:30:27.050 --> 00:30:28.824
<i>You know a lot about "Foul Detective."</i>

466
00:30:28.824 --> 00:30:31.163
<i>Are you asking me to join
the team of writers?</i>

467
00:30:31.163 --> 00:30:32.257
<i>Let's go on a trip.</i>

468
00:30:32.257 --> 00:30:33.302
<i>I came to be a pack mule.</i>

469
00:30:33.302 --> 00:30:35.899
<i>- You have the day off!
- Chef, you're the best!</i>

470
00:30:35.899 --> 00:30:37.217
<i>Let's meet up with Hyun Soo tomorrow.</i>

471
00:30:37.217 --> 00:30:38.780
<i>Fate, disguised as coincidence.</i>

472
00:30:38.780 --> 00:30:39.839
<i>Where do you want to go first?</i>

473
00:30:39.839 --> 00:30:41.822
<i>How did you think of
coming here with me?</i>

474
00:30:41.822 --> 00:30:43.848
<i>Be careful.
Don't get lost.</i>

475
00:30:43.848 --> 00:30:46.000
<i>You can't get lost here!</i>

476
00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:48.195
<i>I thought you said that
you weren't getting lost anymore!</i>

477
00:30:49.841 --> 00:30:51.183
<i>I love you.</i>

478
00:30:51.183 --> 00:30:52.942
<i>I'm in love with you.</i>

479
00:30:52.942 --> 00:30:58.918
<i>[Tomorrow night at 10 p.m…]</i>

480
00:30:58.918 --> 00:31:06.010
<i>[Temperature of Love]</i>

